Kwaito superstar Kabelo Mabalane and Peteni Khuzwayo’s long journey from Johannesburg to Durban is set to get underway this morning. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Kwaito star Kabelo Mabalane and Peteni Khuzwayo will start their long journey from Johannesburg to Durban, on Monday morning. The duo will be on the road for 17-days, averaging a speed of about 35-kilometres per day. READ: New addition to the Mabalane family They aim to raise R6-million for Joint Aid Management, which feeds to over 100,000 needy children across the country. Mabalane and Khuzwayo have ran the Comrades Marathon several times. They set off at 8:30am.